Giovanni M. Di Liberto received B.E. and M.E. degrees in Information Engineering and in Computer Engineering from University of Padua (Universita' degli Studi di Padova), Italy, in 2011 and 2013 respectively. He was a visiting student at University College Cork (Cork Constraint Computation Centre), Ireland, between 2012 and 2013, and he is currently working towards a Ph.D. degree in the department of Electronic and Electrical Engineering, University of Dublin, Trinity College, Ireland.
His current research is centered around the human auditory system, in particular on the development of methodologies to model and quantify cortical activity in response to natural speech.

